Business Insights Report

E-Commerce Sales Analysis
Project Overview
This report summarizes the key findings from the E-Commerce Sales Analysis Project, where transactional retail data was analysed using SQL and Tableau to identify sales trends, customer purchasing behaviour, and product performance.
The dataset contains online retail transactions including invoice details, products sold, quantities, prices, customer IDs, and country information.
The objective of this analysis was to uncover insights that can help businesses improve sales strategy, customer engagement, and product management.
________________________________________
1. Sales Performance Insights
Overall Revenue
The dataset analysis shows that the company generated significant revenue from online retail transactions across multiple countries.
Revenue was calculated using:
Revenue = Quantity × Unit Price
This metric allowed us to measure total business performance across transactions.
________________________________________
2. Monthly Revenue Trend
The monthly sales analysis revealed fluctuations in revenue across different months.
Key observations:
• Revenue tends to increase during certain periods, indicating seasonal demand.
• Sales spikes may align with holiday shopping periods or promotional campaigns.
• Monitoring monthly trends helps businesses forecast demand and manage inventory effectively.
________________________________________
3. Geographic Sales Distribution
Revenue by Country
Sales data shows that revenue is concentrated in a few key countries.
Key insights:
• A small number of countries generate the majority of revenue.
• This suggests strong market penetration in those regions.
• Businesses can focus marketing efforts on high-performing regions while exploring opportunities in emerging markets.
________________________________________
4. Product Performance
Top Performing Products
Analysis of product sales revealed that certain products consistently generate higher revenue and sales volume.
Key insights:
• A small percentage of products contribute significantly to total revenue.
• These high-performing products should be prioritized for stock availability and marketing promotions.
• Understanding product performance helps optimize inventory management.
________________________________________
5. Customer Behaviour Analysis
Top Customers
Customer analysis showed that some customers contribute significantly more revenue than others.
Key insights:
• High-value customers play an important role in total sales.
• Businesses should consider loyalty programs or personalized marketing strategies for these customers.
• Identifying repeat customers can help improve customer retention.
________________________________________
6. Daily Sales Patterns
Daily sales analysis highlighted fluctuations in purchasing activity.
Key insights:
• Some days show unusually high sales activity.
• Sales spikes may correspond to promotions or seasonal demand.
• Monitoring daily sales trends helps businesses respond quickly to market demand.
________________________________________
7. Business Recommendations
Based on the analysis, the following recommendations can help improve business performance:
• Focus marketing efforts on top-performing countries.
• Promote high-performing products to increase revenue.
• Implement loyalty programs for high-value customers.
• Use historical sales trends for better inventory planning.
• Monitor daily sales activity to detect unusual patterns.
________________________________________
Conclusion
This project demonstrates how SQL and data visualization tools such as Tableau can be used to transform raw transactional data into meaningful business insights.
Through data cleaning, aggregation, and visualization, the analysis identified key patterns in sales performance, customer behaviour, and product demand.
These insights can support data-driven decision making for businesses operating in the e-commerce industry.
